2. Approach

sir &lt;- function(time, state, params) {
  with(as.list(c(state, params)), {
    N  &lt;- S + I + R
    dS &lt;- -beta * S * I / N
    dI &lt;-  beta * S * I / N - gamma * I
    dR &lt;-  gamma * I
    list(c(dS, dI, dR))
  })
}

4. Check
Peak prevalence and attack rate should rise with R₀.

trajectories |&gt;
  filter(compartment == "I") |&gt;
  group_by(R0) |&gt;
  summarise(peak_I = max(n), peak_day = time[which.max(n)]) |&gt;
  arrange(R0)

